      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BAYBOUGG (7) won four back and has been within range her three since. Switching to the synthetic won't be an issue and she's well placed with the handy 2kg claim. Has the inside gate and will get every chance to return to the winners' list. AGNETE (4) came from well back on the bend to score last time out over 1400m at Launceston. That was deserved and she boasts a sound record at this track and trip. A winning contender. WHIPPIN PICCADILLY (2) was seeking the hat-trick at Launceston last time but found the grade too rich. The top hoop rides for the first time and that's a decent push for her chances. Finds a more suitable race and has to be considered. FLYING BILLIE (1) improved last start but found one better over 1430m at Hobart, beaten just 1.3 lengths. No surprise to see him right in contention.",
